6quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20close-range%20air-to-air%20combat%20between%20two%20aircraft%2C%20traditionally%20crewed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFlying%20the%20drone%2C%20he%20explained%2C%20is%20just%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdrone-warfare-isnt-like-video-games-gamers-make-great-pilots-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eusing%20a%20video%20game%20controller%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20other%20Ukrainian%20pilots%20have%20noted%20as%20well.%20Operators%20previously%20told%20BI%20that%20gamers%20tend%20to%20make%20pretty%20good%20pilots.%20But%20this%20war%20is%20very%20different%20from%20a%20game%2C%20as%20battlefield%20decisions%20come%20with%20very%20real%20life-and-death%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Ukrainian%20soldier%20holds%20a%20fake%20bomb%20attached%20to%20a%20flying%20drone%20in%20a%20grassy%20field%20with%20a%20blue%20sky%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67378aa6192f52589858e2a4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223602%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDrones%20have%20defined%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20with%20Russian%20and%20Ukrainian%20forces%20adapting%20to%20challenges%20in%20real%20time.%3Cp%3EPaula%20Bronstein%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EButcher%2C%20originally%20a%20chef%20at%20home%20in%20Canada%2C%20traveled%20to%20Ukraine%20in%20early%202023%20and%20joined%20up%20with%20an%20organization%20cooking%20for%20troops%20on%20the%20front%20lines.%20Ukrainian%20culture%20was%20a%20big%20aspect%20of%20his%20upbringing%2C%20but%20he%20had%20lost%20the%20language%20and%20grew%20away%20from%20the%20community%20as%20he%20got%20older.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%202014%2C%20when%20Russia%20annexed%20Crimea%20and%20began%20seizing%20territories%20in%20the%20Donbas%20region%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20started%20paying%20more%20attention%20to%20what%20was%20happening%2C%26quot%3B%20Butcher%20said.%20He%20was%20propelled%20to%20action%20after%20the%202022%20full-scale%20invasion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%202023%2C%20he%20began%20working%20to%20provide%20aid%20with%20a%20non-governmental%20organization%20after%20the%20destruction%20of%20the%20Kakhovka%20Dam%20east%20of%20Kherson.%20He%20remained%20involved%20in%20humanitarian%20and%20military%20aid%20for%20months%2C%20also%20helping%20translate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20first%20began%20learning%20about%20combat%20drones%20by%20volunteering%20with%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-wild-hornets-sting-shahed-drones-war-russia-iran-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWild%20Hornets%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20organization%20that%20is%20focused%20on%20providing%20uncrewed%20systems%20for%20Ukraine's%20armed%20forces.%20He%20honed%20other%20combat%20skills%20before%20enlisting%20in%20basic%20training%20last%20fall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20now%20focused%20on%20air%20defenses%2C%20often%20targeting%20drones%20used%20for%20intelligence%2C%20surveillance%2C%20and%20reconnaissance%20operations%2C%20and%20is%20deployed%20in%20the%20Donetsk%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20has%20been%20increasingly%20using%20drones%20to%20intercept%20and%20take%20out%20Russia's%20attack%20drones%20and%20loitering%20munitions%2C%20opting%20to%20use%20them%20as%20cheaper%20options%20over%20air%20defense%20missiles.%20They've%20also%20targeted%20Russian%20intelligence%2C%20surveillance%2C%20and%20reconnaissance%20platforms%20that%20provide%20information%20on%20Ukrainian%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20with%20drones%20has%20come%20with%20a%20learning%20curve%2C%20one%20that%20is%20far%20from%20static.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAfter%20Butcher%20decided%20to%20start%20training%20on%20drones%2C%20he%20began%20with%20different%20sizes%20and%20brands%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdrone-footage-in-ukraine-twists-perc