agents%20and%20explained%20that%20he%20was%20there%20to%20serve%20legal%20documents%20on%20Mr%20Doval%20and%20%26quot%3Bthat%20he%20had%20a%20Court%20Order%20permitting%20service%20of%20the%20documents%20on%20any%20member%20of%20the%20Secret%20Service%20providing%20security%26quot%3B%20during%20the%20NSA's%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe%20showed%20the%20Secret%20Service%20agent%20a%20copy%20of%20this%20Court's%20Order%2C%20but%20the%20agent%20refused%20to%20accept%20any%20documents%20and%20told%20the%20individual%20to%20leave%20the%20checkpoint%2C%26quot%3B%20Pannun%20said%20in%20court%20papers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPannun%20said%20the%20individual%20he%20had%20hired%20to%20deliver%20the%20complaint%20%26quot%3Bfeared%20that%20if%20he%20took%20any%20further%20action%20he%20would%20be%20arrested%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20day%2C%20on%20February%2013%2C%20another%20individual%20attempted%20to%20serve%20the%20documents%20on%20Mr%20Doval%20at%20Blair%20House%20but%20%26quot%3Bthree%20Secret%20Service%20agents%26quot%3B%2C%20including%20a%20sergeant%2C%20stopped%20him%20%26quot%3Bat%20the%20checkpoint%20outside%20Blair%20House%2C%20refused%20to%20allow%20him%20beyond%20the%20checkpoint%2C%20and%20refused%20to%20accept%20any%20documents%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20individual%20told%20the%20agents%20that%20he%20would%20place%20the%20envelope%20containing%20the%20service%20documents%20on%20the%20ground%20in%20front%20of%20them%20but%20one%20of%20the%20agents%20told%20him%20that%20%26quot%3Bif%20he%20left%20the%20documents%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20agents%20would%20arrest%20him%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20individual%20then%20left%20the%20documents%20at%20a%20coffee%20store%20near%20Blair%20House%20and%20told%20the%20Secret%20Service%20agents%20to%20retrieve%20them%20and%20give%20them%20to%20Mr%20Doval.%20In%20court%20papers%2C%20Pannun%20claims%20that%20he%20has%20completed%20the%20process%20of%20serving%20the%20complaint%20on%20Mr%