2content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EDespite%20loud%20whispers%20of%20a%20slowdown%E2%80%94or%20even%20a%20potential%20recession%E2%80%94and%20despite%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20now-chaotic%20tariff%20tantrums%2C%20the%20US%20is%20gaining%20big%20in%20one%20key%20area%20that%20isn't%20being%20talked%20about%20much%3A%20attracting%20capital.%20A%20staggering%20%241.7%20trillion%20in%20foreign%20and%20domestic%20investment%20commitments%2C%20made%20in%20less%20than%20three%20months%2C%20underlines%20long-term%20confidence%20in%20the%20world's%20biggest%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20companies%20like%20Apple%20and%20TSMC%2C%20and%20countries%20such%20as%20Saudi%20Arabia%2C%20bet%20on%20the%20American%20economy%2C%20they%20don't%20do%20it%20on%20a%20whim%3A%20they%20do%20it%20because%20they%20see%20long-term%20profitability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20pugilist-like%20tariff%20jabs%20may%20be%20earning%20him%20more%20adversaries%20than%20he%20bargained%20for%2C%20but%20he%20has%20been%20demonstrating%20his%20knack%20for%20convincing%20countries%20and%20corporations%20to%20invest%20big%20in%20the%20US%20economy%20to%20maintain%20its%20economic%20edge.%20Amid%20the%20doom%20and%20gloom%20about%20a%20potential%20US%20recession%2C%20one%20cannot%20overlook%20the%20sheer%20gravitational%20pull%20of%20its%20market%E2%80%94and%20indeed%2C%20the%20president's%20personal%20pull.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Trump%2C%20this%20heavy%20influx%20of%20investment%20should%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20strategic%20counter%20to%20recession%20fears.%20Infrastructure%20projects%2C%20high-tech%20manufacturing%20and%20AI%20development%20may%20act%20as%20a%20buffer%20against%20economic%20turbulence%20in%20the%20medium%20to%20long%20term.%20If%20these%20investments%20materialise%20as%20promised%2C%20they%20could%20stabilise%20growth%20and%20reinforce%20America's%20position%20as%20the%20world's%20leading%20innovation%20hub.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBillion-Dollar%20Promises%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetween%20January%2020%E2%80%94when%20Donald%20Trump%20took%20the%20oath%20for%20a%20second%20time%E2%80%94and%20the%20end%20of%20March%2C%20three%20major%20investment%20commitments%20stood%20out%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%C2%A0Saudi%20Arabia%20pledged%20a%20massive%20%24600%20billion%20investment%20in%20the%20US%20over%20the%20next%20four%20years%2C%20with%20Trump%20hinting%20he%20might%20push%20that%20figure%20to%20%241%20trillion.%20He%20called%20Saudi%20Crown%20Prince%20Mohammed%20bin%20Salman%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfantastic%20guy%E2%80%9D%20who%20might%20just%20oblige.%20Typically%2C%20the%20announcement%20by%20the%20Saudis%20remained%20vague%20on%20details.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EApple%20has%20committed%20a%20staggering%20%24500%20billion%20over%20four%20years%2C%20aiming%20to%20create%2020%2C000%20jobs%20and%20establish%20a%20new%20factory%20in%20Houston%20to%20produce%20AI-driven%20server%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20trio%20of%20OpenAI%2C%20Oracle%20and%20SoftBank%20have%20pledged%20%24500%20billion%20for%20a%20project%20dubbed%20Stargate%2C%20designed%20to%20supercharge%20America's%20AI%20infrastructure.%20To%20emphasise%3A%20half%20a%20trillion%20dollars%20in%20investment%20is%20aimed%20at%20keeping%20the%20US%20ahead%20in%20the%20race%20for%20AI%20dominance%20over%20China%20and%20others.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20there%20are%20other%2C%20much%20smaller%2C%20but%20significant%20investment%20commitments%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3ETaiwan%20Semiconductor%20Manufacturing%20Co.%20(TSMC)%20is%20pledging%20%24100%20billion%20in%20the%20US.%20Trump%20himself%20announced%20the%20news%20at%20the%20White%20House%20alongside%20TSMC's%20CEO%2C%20marking%20a%20major%20step%20in%20America's%20effort%20to%20reclaim%20dominance%20in%20semiconductor%20production.%20This%20new%20commitment%20adds%20to%20the%20%2465%20billion%20already%20pledged%20for%20manufacturing%20facilities%20in%20Arizona%2C%20bringing%20TSMC's%20total%20US%20investment%20to%20%24165%20billion.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EEli%20Lilly%20is%20investing%20%2427%20billion%20to%20build%20four%20new%20pharmaceutical%20manufacturing%20plants%2C%20expected%20to%20generate%203%2C000%20high-skilled%20jobs%20and%20employ%2010%2C000%20construction%20workers.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHyundai%20Motor%20Group%20has%20announced%20plans%20to%20invest%20%2421%20billion%20in%20the%20US%20between%202025%20and%202028%20to%20drive%20manufacturing%20growth%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cb%3ESmart%20Focus%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20push%20to%20incentivise%20investment%E2%80%94particularly%20in%20critical%20sectors%20such%20as%20semiconductors%20and%20AI%E2%80%94aligns%20with%20his%20broader%20geopolitical%20strategy.%20For%20example%2C%20by%20encouraging%20TSMC's%20expansion%20in%20the%20US%2C%20his%20administration%20is%20not%20only%20securing%20America's%20access%20to%20advanced%20chip%20technology%E2%80%94a%20vital%20component%20in%20everything%20from%20smartphones%20to%20fighter%20jets%E2%80%94but%20also%20keeping%20China%20at%20bay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20%E2%80%9CAmerica%20First%20Investment%20Policy%E2%80%9D%20memorandum%2C%20issued%20on%20February%2021%2C%20aims%20to%20streamline%20investments%20from%20allies%20while%20tightening%20the%20noose%20on%20China.%20While%20the%20White%20House%20is%20not%20imposing%20immediate%20regulations%2C%20it%20is%20directing%20agencies%20to%20craft%20rules%20that%20ease%20inbound%20investments%20from%20friendly%20nations%20while%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20US%20money%20to%20flow%20to%20adversaries%20like%20China%E2%80%94a%20continuation%20of%20the%20administration's%20broader%20strategy%20to%20decouple%20from%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPromises%2C%20Just%20Promises%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20beyond%20the%20hype%20and%20hoopla%2C%20the%20real%20question%20remains%3A%20how%20much%20of%20this%20investment%20will%20actually%20materialise%3F%20Will%20TSMC's%20chips%20ever%20roll%20off%20Texas%20assembly%20lines%20at%20the%20promised%20scale%3F%20Will%20Apple%20really%20pour%20half%20a%20trillion%20dollars%20into%20the%20US%20economy%2C%20or%20is%20this%20another%20PR%20stunt%20with%20creative%20accounting%3F%20And%20will%20the%20Saudis%20follow%20through%20this%20time%2C%20or%20will%20their%20billions%20once%20again%20remain%20a%20mirage%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20we%20have%20seen%20this%20playbook%20before%20during%20President%20Trump's%20first%20administration%20when%20foreign%20investment%20pledges%20made%20headlines.%20Some%20may%20still%20remember%20the%20much-hyped%20%24350%20billion%20Saudi%20investment%20promise.%20By%20the%20US%20government's%20own%20account%2C%20only%20a%20fraction%20of%20it%20has%20actually%20materialised%20so%20far.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20FDIs%20into%20the%20US%20have%20witnessed%20more%20dips%20than%20peaks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%20Caution%20Prevail%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20then%2C%20let%20us%20not%20forget%20the%20latest%20spanner%20in%20the%20works.%20While%20Trump%20boasts%20about%20foreign%20investment%2C%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20is%20busy%20reminding%20everyone%20that%20inflation%20is%20still%20lurking%2C%20interest%20rates%20remain%20high%20and%20the%20cost%20of%20borrowing%20is%20not%20exactly%20investor-friendly.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20US%20dollar%20recently%20suffered%20its%20worst%20stretch%20since%20November%202022%2C%20dropping%20by%203.4%25.%20Add%20to%20that%20Germany's%20plans%20for%20massive%20spending%20on%20defence%20and%20infrastructure%E2%80%94potentially%20fuelling%20an%20economic%20boost%20in%20Europe%20while%20Washington%20dithers%20on%20Ukraine%20aid%E2%80%94and%20the%20global%20investment%20landscape%20starts%20to%20look%20a%20little%20less%20predictable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%202.0%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20the%20grand%20revival%20of%20%26quot%3BAmerica%20First%26quot%3B%2C%20with%20trade%20tariffs%20acting%20as%20the%20magic%20wand%20to%20resuscitate%20US%20manufacturing%2C%20safeguard%20jobs%20and%20fill%20government%20coffers.%20Instead%2C%20markets%20and%20investors%20have%20been%20left%20jittery.%20Trump%20himself%20isn't%20exactly%20radiating%20confidence%2C%20at%20least%20not%20all%20the%20time.%20A%20few%20weeks%20ago%2C%20he%20even%20hinted%20at%20a%20looming%20recession%2C%20branding%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bperiod%20of%20transition%E2%80%9D.%20Treasury%20Secretary%20Scott%20Bessent%20is%20already%20preparing%20the%20public%20for%20economic%20turbulence%2C%20calling%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bdetox%20period%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESmoke%20And%20Mirrors%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20is%20that%20investors%E2%80%94no%20matter%20how%20much%20they%20may%20like%20Trump's%20tax%20cuts%20and%20deregulation%E2%80%94detest%20uncertainty.%20And%20nothing%20about%20Trump%202.0%20suggests%20a%20stable%2C%20predictable%20business%20environment.%20Trade%20policies%20are%20in%20flux%2C%20tariffs%20could%20rise%20overnight%2C%20and%20global%20allies%20are%20less%20inclined%20to%20play%20along%20with%20Washington's%20demands.%20The%20market%20remains%20on%20edge%2C%20with%20businesses%20and%20economists%20alike%20bracing%20for%20whatever%20comes%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20will%20these%20investment%20pledges%20turn%20into%20economic%20gold%2C%20or%20are%20we%20looking%20at%20another%20round%20of%20smoke%20and%20mirrors%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20time%20will%20tell%2C%20as%20the%20clich%C3%A9%20goes.%20However%2C%20this%20time%2C%20Trump%20appears%20more%20organised%2C%20more%20ready%20and%20even%20more%20aggressive.%20He%20seems%20less%20willing%20to%20tolerate%20delays.%20The%20mantra%20of%20%26quot%3Beconomic%20nationalism%26quot%3B%20is%20back%20with%20a%20vengeance.%20He%20wants%20to%20do%20onshore%20manufacturing.%20He%20has%20slapped%20tariffs%20on%20imports.%20And%20some%20might%20say%20he%20has%20bullied%20vulnerable%20allies%20into%20economic%20deals%20that%20put%20%E2%80%9CAmerica%20First%E2%80%9D.%20Many%20are%20ready%20to%20bet%20that%20this%20strongman%20approach%20could%20actually%20deliver.%20At%20least%20Trump%20believes%20it%20would.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Syed%20Zubair%20Ahmed%20is%20a%20London-based%20senior%20Indian%20journalist%20with%20three%20decades%20of%20experience%20with%20the%20Western%20media)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743514020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-02%2Fbb8spano_donald-trump_625x300_12_February_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhat-recession-why-investors-have-pledged-1-7-trillion-for-trumps-america-8062388%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Trump's%20pugilist-like%20tariff%20jabs%20may%20be%20earning%20him%20more%20adversaries%20than%20he%20bargained%20for%2C%20but%20he%20has%20demonstrated%20his%20knack%20for%20convincing%20countries%20and%20corporations%20to%20invest%20big%20in%20the%20US.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fwhat-recession-why-investors-have-pledged-1-7-trillion-for-trumps-america-8062388%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22MFI%20loans%20down%2041.7%25%20to%2011.9%20million%20in%20Dec%20quarter%2C%20NPAs%20zoom%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743513690000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fmfi-loans-down-41-7-to-11-9-million-in-dec-quarter-npas-zoom-report-125040101027_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20amount%20disbursed%20to%20the%20borrowers%20who%20come%20from%20the%20poor%20and%20marginalized%20communities%20declined%2034.9%20per%20cent%20to%20Rs%2063%2C440%20crore%20as%20again