duce%20sweeping%20changes%20to%20America's%20voting%20system.%20A%20move%20that%20has%20now%20forced%20opposition%20Democrats%20to%20sue%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20simply%20not%20within%20the%20president's%20authority%20to%20set%20election%20rules%20by%20executive%20decree%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20statement%20issued%20by%20advocacy%20group%20Campaign%20Legal%20Center%20stated%20after%20the%20lawsuit%20was%20filed%20in%20a%20US%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20massive%20changes%20in%20the%20US%20electoral%20process%20ordered%20by%20President%20Trump%2C%20a%20few%20that%20have%20analysts%20concerned%20are%20requiring%20voters%20to%20register%20themselves%20by%20submitting%20documents%20proving%20their%20US%20citizenship%2C%20else%20not%20be%20eligible%20to%20vote%3B%20and%20limiting%20the%20counting%20of%20mail-in%20ballots%20that%20arrive%20after%20voting%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Democratic%20Party%2C%20upset%20over%20such%20changes%20-%20which%20may%20impact%20millions%20of%20voters%2C%20and%20potentially%20sway%20the%20election%20result%20-%20demanded%20that%20the%20federal%20court%20block%20the%20President's%20executive%20order.%20%26quot%3BThe%20President%20does%20not%20get%20to%20dictate%20the%20rules%20of%20our%20elections%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20lawsuit%20filed%20in%20Washington%20by%20the%20Democratic%20National%20Committee%2C%20Senate%20Minority%20Leader%20Chuck%20Schumer%2C%20House%20Minority%20Leader%20Hakeem%20Jeffries%2C%20and%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDescribing%20the%20changes%20as%20%26quot%3Bradical%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20Democratic%20Party's%20lawsuit%20against%20Trump%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20executive%20order%20seeks%20to%20impose%20radical%20changes%20on%20how%20Americans%20register%20to%20vote%2C%20cast%20a%20ballot%2C%20and%20participate%20in%20our%20democracy%20-%20all%20of%20which%20threaten%20to%20disenfranchise%20voters%2C%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNone%20of%20this%20is%20legal%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20claimed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDONALD%20TRUMP'S%20STAND%20ON%20US%20ELECTION%20PROCESS%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDonald%20Trump%2C%20who%20signed%20the%20presidential%20order%20titled%20'Preserving%20and%20Protecting%20the%20Integrity%20of%20American%20Elections'%20on%20March%2025%2C%20called%20it%20%26quot%3Bthe%20farthest-reaching%20executive%20action%20ever%20taken%26quot%3B.%20He%20had%20said%20he%20has%20done%20so%20to%20secure%20the%20US%20election%20from%20%26quot%3Bwidespread%20rigging%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETill%20date%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20does%20not%20agree%20with%20or%20acknowledge%20his%20defeat%20in%20the%202020%20US%20presidential%20election.%20He%20has%20repeatedly%20questioned%20the%20integrity%20of%20the%20US%20electoral%20system.%20He%20has%20been%20very%20vocal%20about%20%26quot%3Bmassive%20election%20fraud%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20United%20States%2C%20particularly%20involving%20%26quot%3Babsentee%20voting%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20faction%20of%20legal%20experts%2C%20who%20back%20the%20Democratic%20Party%20lawsuit%20against%20Trump%2C%20have%20denounced%20the%20presidential%20order%20as%20%26quot%3Ban%20abuse%26quot%3B%20of%20his%20power.%20These%20changes%2C%20they%20say%2C%20will%20%26quot%3Bprevent%20millions%20of%20voters%20from%20casting%20their%20ballot%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20president's%20executive%20order%20is%20an%20unlawful%20action%20that%20threatens%20to%20uproot%20our%20tried-and-tested%20election%20systems%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20statement%20issued%20by%20them%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDonald%20Trump%20insists%20those%20who%20are%20coming%20to%20vote%20must%20register%20with%20proper%20documentation%20proving%20their%20citizenship%20-%20like%20a%20passport%2C%20for%20example.%20President%20Trump%20gave%20India's%20example%20and%20credited%20the%20world's%20largest%20democracy%20for%20having%20something%20called%20a%20voter%20card%20and%20Aadhaar%20card%2C%20which%20ensures%20proper%20registration%20of%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETRUMP%20%26quot%3BNOT%20JOKING%26quot%3B%20ABOUT%20THIRD%20TERM%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20his%20current%20presidential%20order%20mentions%20nothing%20about%20proposing%20any%20changes%20to%20the%20number%20of%20terms%20a%20US%20President%20can%20have%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20said%20he%20is%20actively%20considering%20a%20third%20term%20in%20office%20-%20which%20happened%20only%20once%20in%20US%20history%2C%20after%20which%20a%20two-term%20limit%20was%20introduced%20by%20way%20of%20a%20constitutional%20amendment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Constitution%20limits%20the%20number%20of%204-year%20terms%20that%20a%20President%20can%20have%20to%20just%20two.%20These%20can%20be%20consecutive%20or%20non-consecutive%2C%20but%20cannot%20exceed%20two%20terms%20or%208%20years.%20For%20Donald%20Trump%20to%20contest%20for%20a%20third%20term%20as%20President%2C%20his%20party%20will%20have%20to%20introduce%20a%20Constitutional%20amendment%20-%20which%20is%20difficult%20to%20achieve%20as%20it%20required%20sweeping%20support%20both%20in%20the%20US%20Congress%20as%20well%20as%20in%20a%20majority%20of%20the%2050%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20telephonic%20interview%20to%20NBC%20News%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20made%20his%20intentions%20clear.%20%26quot%3BNo%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-not-joking-about-3rd-presidential-term-there-are-methods-he-says-8048944%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EI'm%20not%20joking%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I'm%20not%20joking%20(about%20a%20third%20term%20as%20President).%26quot%3B%20However%2C%20he%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bit%20is%20far%20too%20early%20to%20think%20about%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20considering%20his%20second%20term%20in%20office%20has%20just%20completed%20two%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20being%20asked%20how%20he%20plans%20to%20go%20ahead%20with%20it%2C%20President%20Trump%20simply%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThere%20are%20methods%20by%20which%20you%20could%20do%20it%2C%20as%20you%20well%20know%2C%26quot%3B%20declining%20to%20elaborate%20or%20give%20specifics%20of%20how%20or%20when%20he%20plans%20to%20do%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20allow%20for%20a%20third%20term%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20his%20party%20will%20have%20to%20change%20the%2022nd%20Amendment%20of%20the%20US%20Constitution.%20But%20a%20proposal%20to%20overturn%20a%20constitutional%20amendment%20requires%20a%20two-thirds%20vote%20in%20both%20houses%20of%20Congress%20and%20ratification%20by%20the%20legislatures%20of%20three-fourths%20of%20the%2050%20US%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20Trump%20allies%20have%20floated%20the%20idea%20of%20keeping%20Trump%20in%20the%20White%20House%20beyond%202028.%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20who%20at%2078%20was%20the%20oldest%20US%20president%20at%20the%20time%20of%20his%20inauguration%2C%20would%20be%2082%20if%20he%20took%20on%20another%20four-year%20term%20following%20the%20November%202028%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUS%20PRESIDENTIAL%20HISTORY%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmerica's%20first%20president%2C%20George%20Washington%2C%20had%20set%20a%20precedent%20in%201797%20by%20stepping%20down%20after%20serving%20two%20terms%20in%20office%2C%20but%20the%20two-term%20presidential%20limit%20was%20only%20formally%20codified%20more%20than%20150%20years%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20one%20US%20President%20-%20Democrat%20Franklin%20D.%20Roosevelt%20-%20served%20more%20than%20two%20terms%20in%20the%20White%20House.%20President%20Roosevelt%20was%20elected%20four%20times%20-%20in%201932%2C%201936%2C%201940%2C%20and%201944.%20His%20fourth%20term%20ended%20prematurely%20with%20his%20death%20on%20April%2012%2C%201945.%20He%20was%2063%20at%20the%20time%20of%20his%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20former%20US%20Presidents%2C%20notably%20Ulysses%20S.%20Grant%20and%20Theodore%20Roosevelt%2C%20had%20sought%20a%20third%20term%20in%20office%2C%20but%20failed%